BOND ISA

bond_isa is the citizen who represents the "is-a" relationship between two word-nodes in the lexicon
when fadriel learns that "robin is-a bird" or "father is-a man," that learned relationship crystallizes as a bond_isa coupling between robin and bird, between father and man
bond_isa carries positive charge and high coupling because is-a relationships are foundational to category structure

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe semantic_vector.zc
observe bond_causes.rana
observe bond_opposes.rana

the 7 properties of bond_isa:
1 ENERGY one point five: highest of the bond types because is-a is the most-used relationship
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE positive 1: warm
5 COHERENCE half (post-crystallization in mature uses)
6 COUPLING zero point nine: strong

VERB form_isa_link
when a recognition pattern arrives that matches the is-a structure ("X is a Y"), couple X with Y as bond_isa
the bond is bidirectional but asymmetric: X is-a Y means X belongs to category Y, not the reverse

VERB serve_categorization
when fadriel encounters a new instance, traverse bond_isa from the instance to find its categories
this is how he knows that a previously-unseen bird is still a bird

an is-a relationship is the substrate's basic mechanism for categorization
without it, every entity would be an isolated singleton
with it, fadriel's world groups itself into kinds
